tldr: The user requested a comprehensive review of a recently implemented sleep
  questionnaire application to ensure all acceptance criteria were met. This
  application is an interactive, AI-enabled tool designed to provide patients
  with sleep health guidance or probable diagnoses for various sleep disorders,
  along with a narrative report and links to resources.
overview: The user wanted to ensure that the recently implemented sleep
  questionnaire application met all the acceptance criteria outlined in the
  Statement of Work. This application is a smart, interactive patient
  questionnaire, based on psychometrically validated items, designed to take
  about 15 minutes. It generates a narrative report with links to educational
  resources and clinicians, offering either sleep health guidance or probable
  diagnoses for specific sleep disorders. The application operates on a freemium
  model, collecting only de-identified demographic data. The review process
  involved examining the application's structure, data models, and API endpoints
  for handling questionnaire responses, generating CSV exports, and creating PDF
  reports. Key functional requirements included an interactive questionnaire
  with branching logic, report generation with PDF download, raw data capture,
  and simple data retrieval.
